Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a visual-inertial framework for on-board navigation and mapping on a fast-moving aerial platform, which falls under the scope of robotics.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper involves visual processing for estimating camera poses and depth measurements, which is a core area of computer vision.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a probabilistic wing model fused in an EKF formulation, which involves probabilistic modeling and filtering techniques commonly used in machine learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper involves designing a system for estimating camera poses and depth measurements on a non-rigid trinocular baseline, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves developing an intelligent system for on-board navigation and mapping, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence.
